Proverbs 19-18 <t><f>ⓘ</f> Discipline your son, for there is hope; </t><t>do not set your heart on <f>ⓙ</f>putting him to death.</t>
Proverbs 19-19 <t>A man of great wrath will pay the penalty, </t><t>for if you deliver him, you will only have to do it again.</t>
Proverbs 19-20 <t>Listen to advice and accept instruction, </t><t>that you may gain wisdom in <f>ⓚ</f>the future.</t>
